# CohortLens — Monorepo

## Layout

- `packages/frontend` — Next.js (App Router), Tailwind, Wagmi/Viem, React Query.
- `packages/backend-ai` — FastAPI, clustering, GraphQL clients (subgraphs), and **web3.py** for contracts.
- `packages/indexers` — The Graph subgraphs per protocol and chain (`protocols/<protocol>/<chain>/`).
- `packages/contracts` — Solidity (Foundry), e.g. `CohortOracle`.

## On-chain data and indexing (The Graph)

- One subgraph per protocol and network under `packages/indexers/protocols/<protocol>/<chain>/`: `subgraph.yaml`, `schema.graphql`, `src/mapping.ts`, `abis/*.json`.
- **AssemblyScript** in `mapping.ts`; versioned entities; deterministic IDs (e.g. `txHash-logIndex`).
- Deployment: local **Graph Node** (compose at repo root) or **Subgraph Studio / hosted network**; the backend only consumes the GraphQL HTTP query URL (`SUBGRAPH_URL`).
- Do not mix indexing logic into the Python backend: the backend aggregates and queries; the subgraph indexes events.

## Backend Python (`packages/backend-ai`)

- **FastAPI** + **Pydantic v2**; strict typing; no `any`.
- Reading indexed data: GraphQL client with **timeouts**, pagination (`first`/`skip`), and explicit handling of GraphQL `errors` in the JSON response.
- EVM contracts: **web3.py** only (viem is for the TypeScript frontend).
- Async work outside the request: **Celery** with **Redis** broker/backend; idempotent tasks; block pointers in Redis or DB for event scanners.
- Private keys (`ORACLE_OWNER_PRIVATE_KEY`, transaction signers) only in environment variables, never in code or public images.

## AI models and marketplace (`packages/backend-ai`)

- Model artifacts are published on **IPFS** (CID); the `CohortRegistry` contract stores `modelHash` (string with CID or IPFS path).
- Supported inference formats: **pickle/joblib (scikit-learn)** and **ONNX** (`onnxruntime`). Pickle is inherently unsafe if the source is untrusted: only audited models or ones generated by the operator.
- Heavy inference and training go to **Celery** (app `app/tasks/celery_app.py`) with separate queues: `ml_tasks`, `prediction_tasks`, `zk_tasks`; tasks live under `app/tasks/*.py`.
- Prediction endpoints must support **wallet signature authentication** (message with nonce, EIP-191) when `REQUIRE_WALLET_AUTH=true`, and **rate limiting** (e.g. SlowAPI) on sensitive routes.
- Extra metadata (model type: churn, LTV, etc.) may live in Postgres; the contract already includes `name` and `description`.

## Phase 6 — Scalability and decentralization

- **Celery + Redis**: all heavy AI work is asynchronous; dedicated queues (`ml_tasks` for clustering/oracle scan/training, `prediction_tasks` for inference, `zk_tasks` for ZK proofs); idempotent tasks and retries on distributed workers.
- **Multi-chain**: the backend resolves chain via configuration (`CHAINS_JSON` or equivalent): each chain has its own `subgraph_url`, RPC, and contract addresses; no indexing logic in Python.
- **Akash Network**: optional worker deployment under `deploy/akash/` (SDL + docs); Docker image of the backend with Celery; the Redis broker must be reachable from the deployment network.
- **Zero-knowledge proofs (EZKL)**: generate proofs that certify model execution without exposing private data; register the **proof hash** on-chain (`CohortOracle`) for auditing; full SNARK verification stays off-chain.
- **Distributed cache**: Redis for frequent clustering results; **Prometheus** (and optionally Grafana) for latency, errors, and queue visibility.

## Phase 7 — Tokenomics and governance

- **New contracts** must follow **OpenZeppelin** patterns: **ERC20** + **ERC20Votes** (for governance), **Governor** + **TimelockController**; avoid ad-hoc governance. Economic parameters should be governable via Timelock where appropriate.
- **Staking**: model creators **lock LENS** in `Staking`; **`CohortRegistry.registerLens`** requires a **minimum staked balance** (read from `Staking`, immutable reference or Timelock-only setter).
- **Per-query payments**: users pay in **LENS** through **`CohortOracle.requestPrediction`** (`transferFrom` after `approve`/`permit`); the oracle splits fees between the **lens owner**, a **rewards pool** (typically `Staking`), and optionally **treasury**.
- **Governance**: **OpenZeppelin Governor** (not Governor Bravo unless explicitly justified) + **Timelock**; **ERC20Votes** holders (stakers who delegate) vote on **parameter updates** and **slashing** (e.g. proposals that call `Staking.slash` and `CohortRegistry.setLensActive` to disable malicious models).

---

# CohortLens — Frontend (packages/frontend)

## Stack

- **Next.js 14+** with the **App Router** (`app/`). Do not add new routes under `pages/` unless migrating legacy code.
- **Exception (Phase 7)**: tokenomics UIs may live under `pages/staking.tsx` and `pages/governance.tsx` for staking and governance screens.
- **TypeScript** strict mode; no `any` unless justified with a short comment.
- **Tailwind CSS** for styling; prefer utility classes and small `@layer` additions in `styles/globals.css` over ad-hoc CSS files.
- **Wagmi v2** + **Viem** for wallets; **TanStack React Query** for server state (mutations/queries).
- **Axios** for HTTP clients in `lib/` / hooks when centralizing API calls.

## Project layout (packages/frontend)

- `app/` — routes, `layout.tsx`, `page.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `providers.tsx` (client providers only).
- `components/ui/` — **atoms**: buttons, inputs, small presentational pieces (e.g. `WalletButton`).
- `components/cohort/` — **domain / organisms**: cohort-specific UI (e.g. `CohortTable`).
- `components/layout/` — **templates**: headers, footers, shells shared across routes.
- `hooks/` — custom hooks (`useWallet`, `useCohortApi`); prefix with `use`.
- `lib/` — config, API clients, wagmi config, env helpers; no JSX.
- `styles/` — `globals.css` and global Tailwind entry.
- `types/` — shared TypeScript types and DTOs aligned with the backend.

## Conventions

- **Files**: kebab-case for route segments; **components** PascalCase (`WalletButton.tsx`).
- **Exports**: prefer named exports for components and hooks.
- **Components**: functional components only; explicit prop types/interfaces.
- **Data fetching**: use React Query (`useMutation` / `useQuery`) for API calls; surface loading and error states in the UI.
- **Wallets**: wrap the tree with `WagmiProvider` + `QueryClientProvider` in a single client `Providers` component in `app/providers.tsx`.
- **Errors**: use `app/error.tsx` (and `global-error.tsx` when needed) for route-level failures; show actionable retry UI.
- **Atomic design**: atoms in `ui/`, feature blocks in `cohort/` or `layout/`, compose in `app/` pages.

## API

- Base URL: `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL ?? "http://localhost:8000"`.
- Cohort discovery: `POST /api/v1/cohorts/discover` — request/response types live in `types/cohort.ts` and must match the FastAPI schemas.
- Model marketplace: routes under `app/marketplace/`, `app/models/[id]/` — types in `types/models.ts` aligned with `/api/v1/models`.

## Do not

- Inline dynamic `import()` inside components for libraries that belong at the top of the file.
- Bypass React Query for duplicated fetch logic when mutations/queries are already standardized in hooks.

## Phase 8 — Production and open source

- **Secrets**: never commit secrets or private keys. Use environment variables, GitHub Actions secrets, and secret managers only. Document non-secret variable names in `.env.example` / `.env.production.example`.
- **Structured logging**: in production, prefer JSON logs (e.g. `structlog` or JSON `Formatter`) with consistent fields (`level`, `message`, `timestamp`); set log level via `LOG_LEVEL`.
- **Observability**: keep **Prometheus** metrics for HTTP and queues; add **Sentry** for error tracking when `SENTRY_DSN` is set (`SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT` for staging/production). Do not log PII or raw request bodies to third parties.
- **Versioning**: follow **SemVer** for releases (`vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`); use **git-cliff** and [RELEASE.md](RELEASE.md) for changelog and tagging. Contract deployments are recorded under `packages/contracts/deployments/`.
- **Documentation site**: maintain the Docusaurus project under [docs/](docs/) (architecture, deployment, API reference, security). See [.cursor/skills/cohortlens-production-docs/SKILL.md](.cursor/skills/cohortlens-production-docs/SKILL.md).
- **CI/CD**: GitHub Actions runs tests, linters, Slither/Mythril (policy in [docs/docs/security.md](docs/docs/security.md)), and Docker builds. Prefer manual approval and multisig (e.g. Gnosis Safe) for mainnet operations over long-lived keys in CI.
